#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.22:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.22:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga"
msgstr "3. Māra"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.22:0.3"
msgid "22. Samiddhisutta"
msgstr "22. With Samiddhi"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.119"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.263"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.22:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati silāvatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans near Silāvatī."

msgctxt "sn4.22:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā samiddhi bhagavato avidūre appamatto ātāpī "
"pahitatto viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Samiddhi was meditating not far from the Buddha, "
"diligent, keen, and resolute."

msgctxt "sn4.22:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmato samiddhissa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso "
"parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Then as Venerable Samiddhi was in private retreat this thought came to his "
"mind:"

msgctxt "sn4.22:1.4"
msgid "“lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr "“I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "sn4.22:1.5"
msgid "yassa me satthā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho."
msgstr "to have a teacher who is a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha!"

msgctxt "sn4.22:1.6"
msgid "Lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr "I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "sn4.22:1.7"
msgid "yvāhaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajito."
msgstr "to have gone forth in a teaching and training so well explained!"

msgctxt "sn4.22:1.8"
msgid "Lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr "I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "sn4.22:1.9"
msgid "yassa me sabrahmacārino sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā”ti."
msgstr "to have spiritual companions who are ethical and of good character.”"

msgctxt "sn4.22:1.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā āyasmato samiddhissa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya "
"yenāyasmā samiddhi tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmato samiddhissa avidūre "
"mahantaṃ bhayabheravaṃ saddamakāsi, apissudaṃ pathavī maññe undrīyati."
msgstr ""
"And then Māra the Wicked, knowing what Samiddhi was thinking, went up to him "
"and made a terrifyingly loud noise close by him. It seemed as if the earth "
"was shattering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.22:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā samiddhi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno āyasmā samiddhi "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Samiddhi went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told "
"him what had happened. The Buddha said:"

msgctxt "sn4.22:2.2"
msgid "“idhāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato avidūre appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.22:2.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko "
"udapādi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.22:2.4"
msgid "‘lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.22:2.5"
msgid "yassa me satthā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.22:2.6"
msgid "Lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.22:2.7"
msgid "yvāhaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajito."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.22:2.8"
msgid "Lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.22:2.9"
msgid "yassa me sabrahmacārino sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.22:2.10"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, avidūre mahābhayabheravasaddo ahosi, apissudaṃ pathavī "
"maññe undrīyatī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.120"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.264"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.22:3.1"
msgid "“Nesā, samiddhi, pathavī undrīyati."
msgstr "“Samiddhi, that’s not the earth shattering."

msgctxt "sn4.22:3.2"
msgid "Māro eso pāpimā tuyhaṃ vicakkhukammāya āgato."
msgstr "That’s Māra the Wicked come to pull the wool over your eyes!"

msgctxt "sn4.22:3.3"
msgid "Gaccha tvaṃ, samiddhi, tattheva appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharāhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Go back to that same place, Samiddhi, and meditate, diligent, keen, and "
"resolute.”"

msgctxt "sn4.22:3.4"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā samiddhi bhagavato paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Samiddhi. He got up from his seat, bowed, and "
"respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving."

msgctxt "sn4.22:3.5"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho āyasmā samiddhi tattheva appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"And for a second time Samiddhi was meditating in that same place, diligent, "
"ardent, and resolute."

msgctxt "sn4.22:3.6"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmato samiddhissa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa … pe …"
msgstr "And for a second time he had the same thought …"

msgctxt "sn4.22:3.7"
msgid ""
"dutiyampi kho māro pāpimā āyasmato samiddhissa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya "
"… pe …"
msgstr "and Māra made an earth-shattering noise."

msgctxt "sn4.22:3.8"
msgid "apissudaṃ pathavī maññe undrīyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.22:3.9"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā samiddhi māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then Samiddhi addressed Māra the Wicked One in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.22:4.1"
msgid "“Saddhāyāhaṃ pabbajito,"
msgstr "“I went forth out of faith"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.22:4.2"
msgid "agārasmā anagāriyaṃ;"
msgstr "from the lay life to homelessness."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.22:4.3"
msgid "Sati paññā ca me buddhā,"
msgstr "My mindfulness and wisdom are mature,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.22:4.4"
msgid "cittañca susamāhitaṃ;"
msgstr "my mind is serene in immersion."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.22:4.5"
msgid "Kāmaṃ karassu rūpāni,"
msgstr "Make whatever illusions you want,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.22:4.6"
msgid "neva maṃ byādhayissasī”ti."
msgstr "it won’t bother me.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.22:5.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ samiddhi bhikkhū”ti dukkhī dummano "
"tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The mendicant Samiddhi knows me!” miserable "
"and sad, vanished right there."
